רבץ / râbats / raw-bats'
=== Etymology ===

A primitive root; 
=== Verb ===
to crouch (on all four legs folded, like a recumbent animal); by implication to recline, repose, brood, lurk, imbed: - crouch (down), fall down, make a fold, lay (cause to, make to) lie (down), make to rest, sit.